This paper deals with the problem of learning from ambiguously labeled face images, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a Matrix Completion for Ambiguity Resolution (MCar) method, which involves matrix factorization and optimization techniques, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of soft labeling vectors and iterative refinement, which are common in multimedia (MM) and information retrieval (IR) research. Therefore, cs.MM and cs.IR are also possible sub-categories.
